Problem1.m--------------Code for Prolem 1
Problem3.m--------------Code for Problem 3
Problem4_a_to_c.m-------Code for Problem 4 Part a to Part c
Problem4_di.m-----------Code for Problem 4 Part d i)
Pr4oblem4_dii.m---------Code for Problem 4 Part d ii)
Problem4_e.m------------Code for Problem 4 Part e
feature.py--------------Python code to generate features for spam filter
trainDigit.m------------Code for training of Gaussian classifier of digit partitioning
                        [mu,sigma]=train(train_data, train_label,type)
                        * type is used to specify i) or ii)
testDigit.m-------------Code for test of Gaussian classifier of digit partitioning
                        [error,prediction] = testDigit(testData,testLabel,mu,inv_sigma,dtSigma,Prior,type);
                        * inv_sigma is used to store the inverse of covariance matrices
                        * dtSigma is used to store the determinants of covariance matrices
                        * Prior is the prior distribution
                        * type is used to specify i) or ii)
trainSpam.m-------------Code for training of Gaussian classifier of digit partitioning
                        [mu,sigma]=train(train_data, train_label,type)
                        * type is used to specify i) or ii)
testSpam.m--------------Code for test of Gaussian classifier of digit partitioning
                        [error,prediction] = testDigit(testData,testLabel,mu,inv_sigma,dtSigma,Prior,type);
                        * inv_sigma is used to store the inverse of covariance matrices
                        * dtSigma is used to store the determinants of covariance matrices
                        * Prior is the prior distribution
                        * type is used to specify i) or ii)
logMultiNormal.m--------Code for calculate the log likelyhood
                        P = logMultiNormal(x,mu,inv_sigma,dtSigma,type )
                        * P is a 10*1 vector that stores the probability of a points in each of the classes
                        * inv_sigma is used to store the inverse of covariance matrices
                        * dtSigma is used to store the determinants of covariance matrices
                        * type is used to specify i) or ii)    
ni.mat------------------Prior distribution if digits.                    
